I’m so happy to have met the lot of you on these apps and through a genuine love a gaming. Cheers to more anniversary’s. 🥂
But in the end, streaming is what I love. Community is my jam. I love people. For as many people who show me their true colours, there are  5 more blossoming in front me. 🖤🖤
I’ve burned out more than I care to admit, convinced myself I wasn’t good enough and lost my high CCV from lack of consistency and I’ve probably quit streaming 20x’s - along with username changes 😂

But, streaming hasn’t always been easy. I’ve lost friends as quickly as I made some, I lost one’s who I thought were real ones… I was targeted by a hate group, I’ve watched my favourite creators get hate raided and harassed cuz they were black.
Streaming has allowed me to meet so many beautiful, kind people. I found me - and came out as non-binary, bisexual.
Best memories: My first bday on stream was the best birthday I’ve ever had. I also can’t forget the raid I got from @claresiobhan which shook me to the core.

Tomorrow is my 2 Year Twitchaversary… I’m a little emotional because I’ve changed so much since that first stream and I’ve accomplished so much…

Biggest accomplishment: I put together over 7 streamathons and helped raise over $18000 in charity as a collective since May 2020.

I haven't been ok, but I've been trying.
I'm not perfect and never claimed I was - but ganging up on someone publicly after they reached out privately is disgusting.
Now, I realize that for the last 2 months it hasn't been Dysmorphia, folks have been holding a grudge about a community group I left and no one thought it was ok to talk to me.
But, I always try to be understanding despite my brain telling me the world hates me, that I'm a fucking loser and no one likes me because I know that others are going through things too.

See these relationships we make with folks online can be hard to navigate when dealing with mental health and rejection dysmorphia is real but truly, no one asked me how I was doing. I was left on read a lot of the time just saying hi.
I JUST moved across the country because my Chronic Illness, mental health blended with the pandemic hit my family hard. I lost my home...

I stayed in all my close streaming friends' discords and lurked in any stream I could attend. I lost my uncle to addiction and then my dad ditched me before Christmas after not seeing him since my grandmother passed in 2019.

tw/// mental health // death // friendship
